# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Firebase — Admin panel + live content
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# 1. Copy this file to `.env.local` (same folder).
# 2. Fill in each value from Firebase Console:
#      https://console.firebase.google.com/
#      → Project settings (gear icon) → General → Your apps → Web
# 3. Restart `npm run dev` after editing.
# 4. Create an admin user from:
#      Firebase Console → Authentication → Users → Add user
#      (use email/password)
# 5. Turn on Firestore:
#      Firebase Console → Firestore Database → Create database
#      (production mode is fine — add rules below)
# 6. Paste these Firestore rules (Rules tab):
#
#      rules_version = '2';
#      service cloud.firestore {
#        match /databases/{database}/documents {
#          // Anyone can READ published content
#          match /content/{doc} {
#            allow read: if true;
#            allow write: if request.auth != null;
#          }
#        }
#      }
#
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY=
VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=
VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=
VITE_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=
VITE_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=
VITE_FIREBASE_APP_ID=

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Cloudinary — Image + Video uploads (preferred over Firebase Storage)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# 1. Sign up free at https://cloudinary.com (no card needed).
# 2. Dashboard → copy "Cloud name" into VITE_CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME.
# 3. Settings → Upload → Add upload preset.
#      - Signing Mode: Unsigned
#      - Name it (e.g. "dgion_unsigned") and Save.
#    Copy the preset name into VITE_CLOUDINARY_UPLOAD_PRESET.
# 4. Restart `npm run dev`.
#
# Once configured, ALL admin uploads (images + videos) flow to Cloudinary
# automatically. Firebase Storage stays as a fallback for image-only when
# Cloudinary isn't set up.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

VITE_CLOUDINARY_CLOUD_NAME=
VITE_CLOUDINARY_UPLOAD_PRESET=
